execute

public void execute()
             throws au.gov.ansto.bragg.cicada.core.exception.NoneAlgorithmException
Call this method to process the processor framework. The method will feed the current signal into the processor framework, which will triger the processing of the processor chain. The processing is in a new thread which is parallel with the main thread.

loadDataFromFile

public au.gov.ansto.bragg.dra.data.databag.GroupData loadDataFromFile(java.lang.String filename)
                                                               throws java.io.IOException,
                                                                      au.gov.ansto.bragg.dra.data.exception.HdfException
This method load a databag from a given file path. The file path is a full path of an hdf file. The return signal of the method is an instance of GroupData, which is a databag that contains the structure of the hdf file, e.g., nested groups and cached variables. When this method are called, only group and variable structures are read. The data storages are not loaded into the memory.

Specified by:
loadDataFromFile in interface AlgorithmManager
Parameters:
filename - full path of an hdf file
Returns:
databag in GroupData type
Throws:
java.io.IOException - illegal access to the file system
au.gov.ansto.bragg.dra.data.exception.HdfException - illegal hdf file format
Since:
V2.0
See Also:
au.gov.ansto.bragg.data.fileaccess.databag.CachedVariable
